{"parse":{"title":"William Creech Sr.","pageid":16494906,"revid":723463808,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">Not to be confused with <a href=\"/wiki/William_Creech\" title=\"William Creech\">William Creech</a>.</div>\n<p><b>William Creech Sr.</b> (1845\u20131918) was an <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Philanthropist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Philanthropist\">philanthropist</a>. <b>\"Uncle\" William Creech</b> is remembered for his contributions to improve <a href=\"/wiki/Harlan_County,_Kentucky\" title=\"Harlan County, Kentucky\">Harlan County, Kentucky</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Philanthropic_efforts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Philanthropic efforts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Pine_Mountain_Settlement_School\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Pine Mountain Settlement School</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Gaining_a_post_office\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gaining a post office</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Philanthropic_efforts\">Philanthropic efforts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=William_Creech_Sr.&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Philanthropic efforts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Pine_Mountain_Settlement_School\">Pine Mountain Settlement School</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=William_Creech_Sr.&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Pine Mountain Settlement School\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Uncle William Creech donated 700 acres (2.8&#160;km<sup>2</sup>) of land to establish <a href=\"/wiki/Pine_Mountain_Settlement_School\" title=\"Pine Mountain Settlement School\">Pine Mountain Settlement School</a>, the first educational institution in the area. The school was co-founded in 1913 by <a href=\"/wiki/Katherine_Pettit\" title=\"Katherine Pettit\">Katherine Pettit</a> and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ethel_de_Long_Zande&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ethel de Long Zande (page does not exist)\">Ethel de Long Zande</a> and was designed by architect <a href=\"/wiki/Mary_Rockwell_Hook\" title=\"Mary Rockwell Hook\">Mary Rockwell Hook</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Pine Mountain Settlement School has served many purposes, though its current foci are <a href=\"/wiki/Appalachia\" title=\"Appalachia\">Appalachian</a> cultural education and <a href=\"/wiki/Environmental_education\" title=\"Environmental education\">environmental education</a>.\n</p><p>As Creech said in a letter from 1915,\n</p>\n<blockquote><p>I have heart and cravin' that our people may grow better. I have deeded my land to the Pine Mountain Settlement School to be used for school purposes as long as the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Constitution\" title=\"United States Constitution\">Constitution of the United States</a> stands. Hoping it may make bright and intelligent people after I'm dead and gone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></blockquote>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gaining_a_post_office\">Gaining a post office</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=William_Creech_Sr.&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Gaining a post office\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p>\nAccording to <a href=\"/wiki/Ben_Lucien_Burman\" title=\"Ben Lucien Burman\">Ben Lucien Burman</a> in <i>Children of Noah: Glimpses of Unknown America</i>,</p><blockquote><p>In any <a href=\"/wiki/Rural\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rural\">rural</a> community the mail is always a matter of importance, particularly in a region so isolated as the Cumberlands. Uncle William had decided that <a href=\"/wiki/Pine_Mountain_(ridge)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pine Mountain (ridge)\">Pine Mountain</a>'s crying need was a <a href=\"/wiki/Post_office\" title=\"Post office\">post office</a>.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-app_blog_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-app_blog-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></blockquote>\n<p>Creech's efforts to gain a local post office were a struggle because his rural area would not be allowed to have its own post office until it was deemed able to support enough postal business. To stimulate mail delivery, Creech worked with often <a href=\"/wiki/Literacy\" title=\"Literacy\">illiterate</a> residents to request <a href=\"/wiki/Mail_order\" title=\"Mail order\">mail-order</a> catalogs. Following his initial efforts with a more personal campaign, Creech helped residents write letters to their sons, husbands, and boyfriends who were fighting in <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_I\" title=\"World War I\">World War I</a>. Although often requiring the help of literate friends, many soldiers responded with letters home.<sup id=\"cite_ref-app_blog_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-app_blog-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Creech's labor was successful. The <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Postal_Service\" title=\"United States Postal Service\">United States Postal Service</a> was impressed by the quantity of mail, and a post office was established in the area.<sup id=\"cite_ref-app_blog_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-app_blog-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=William_Creech_Sr.&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.alphasigmatau.org/alphasigmatau/?page_id=42\">\"Pine Mountain Settlement School\"</a>. Alpha Sigma Tau<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-03-22</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Pine+Mountain+Settlement+School&amp;rft.pub=Alpha+Sigma+Tau&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.alphasigmatau.org%2Falphasigmatau%2F%3Fpage_id%3D42&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWilliam+Creech+Sr.\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\"><span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot\" title=\"Wikipedia:Link rot\"><span title=\"&#160;Dead link since October 2010\">dead link</span></a></i>&#93;</span></sup></span>\n</li>\n<li 